<h2 id="implementation">Technical Implementation</h2>
<p>The following snippet illustrates how to initialize the Ostrich Quantization kernel within a PyTorch-based training pipeline:</p>
<div class="my-6 rounded-xl bg-slate-950 p-5 font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto text-slate-300 border border-slate-800">
<div class="flex gap-1.5 mb-4">
<div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-red-500/30"></div>
<div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-yellow-500/30"></div>
<div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-500/30"></div>
</div>
<pre><code><span class="text-indigo-400">import</span> ostrich_ai <span class="text-indigo-400">as</span> oai
<span class="text-indigo-400">from</span> ostrich.layers <span class="text-indigo-400">import</span> QuantizedKernel

<span class="text-slate-500"># Initialize the Ostrich optimizer with 4-bit precision</span>
model = oai.Model.from_pretrained(<span class="text-green-400">"ostrich-70b-v4"</span>)
q_config = QuantizedKernel.Config(
    precision=<span class="text-orange-400">4</span>,
    dynamic_sparsity=<span class="text-orange-400">True</span>,
    device_map=<span class="text-green-400">"auto"</span>
)

<span class="text-slate-500"># Compile with hardware acceleration</span>
optimized_model = oai.compile(model, config=q_config)
<span class="text-indigo-400">print</span>(f<span class="text-green-400">"Model optimized: {optimized_model.efficiency_score}"</span>)</code></pre>
</div>
